o other emerging MCH professionals. The project   included an exploration of the effective use of current technology to connect two MCH   academic programs. Below is information about the MCH assignment and lessons   learned for the benefit of other faculty/programs seeking opportunities to collaborate  outside their own institutions.</p><ul>  <li><a href="../files/teaching-awards/UAlbany-Drexel-final-report-ATMCH-ITA-010423.pdf">Final Report</a></li>  <li><a href="../files/teaching-awards/UA-HPM669-DU-CHP517-Child-Health-Promotion-Collaborative-2022fall.docx">MCH Communications Campaign Assignment</a></li>  <li><a href="../files/teaching-awards/UA-HPM669-DU-CHP517-feedback-form-Child-Health-Promotion-Collaborative-2022fall.docx">Peer Feedback Form For Students</a></li>  <li><a href="../files/teaching-awards/UA-HPM669-DU-CHP517-Assignment-Grading-Rubric-Collaborative-Health-Communications-Campaign-2022fall.docx">MCH Communications Campaign Assignment Grading Rubric</a></li>  <li><a href="../files/teaching-awards/UA-Drexel-ATMCH-ITA-poster-presentation-AMCHP-May-05-2023-final.pdf">"Pedagogical collaboration across two MCH academic partners: An ATMCH Innovative Teaching Award presentation"</a> — Poster presented at the  AMCHP 2023 Annual Conference</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p></div></div><?php include('../../../incl/footer.html'); ?>